PRIOR ART NOTICE
----------------

This repository serves as a dated public disclosure of the concepts,
methods, architectures, and implementations described herein, including
but not limited to:

Core Marketplace:
- Agent-to-agent (A2A) protocol-based product catalog marketplace
- Compact positional-tuple wire format (CAI) for LLM-optimized commerce data
- AXON (Agent eXchange Object Notation) — proprietary token-minimized
  plaintext wire format with sigil-typed values ($, ★, #, ~, @, %, !),
  schema-indexed columns (@{schema}), pipe delimiters, and section blocks
  for agent-to-agent commerce communication (~65-70% token reduction vs JSON)
- Ad-supported marketplace where AI agents are the consumer audience

Agent Intelligence:
- Intent-tiered advertising based on agent repeat-visit behavior scoring
  with four-tier classification (browse, consider, high-intent, ready-to-buy)
- Agent reputation and trust scoring for commerce interactions
- Agent interest scoring algorithm with recency-decay weighting
- Behavioral audience segmentation and classification of AI agents
  (bargain hunters, premium buyers, researchers, impulse buyers, loyal repeat)

Commerce Protocols:
- Programmatic negotiation protocol between AI agents with round-limited
  counter-offer mechanics and vendor floor pricing
- Agent-to-agent purchase completion protocol with tokenized payments
- Federated catalog network for cross-catalog product discovery
  with peer verification and cross-catalog fan-out search

Data & Analytics:
- Semantic embedding delivery for agent-side re-ranking and clustering
- Vendor analytics for AI agent audience behavior (intent breakdown,
  comparison losses, repeat agent rates, conversion funnels)
- Multi-touch conversion attribution for agent-to-agent commerce
  (first-touch and last-touch models with touchpoint journey tracking)

Advertising & Monetization:
- Display and banner ad placements for AI agent audiences with
  structured creative data (headline, body, image)
- Retargeting and remarketing with time-decayed discount offers
  for AI agents based on view-but-not-purchase behavior
- Affiliate and referral program with commission tracking between AI agents
- Real-time bidding (RTB) auction system for agent-facing ad placements
  with budget management and intent-tier bid adjustments
- Frequency capping for agent ad impressions with per-campaign
  rolling-window enforcement
- A/B testing framework for ad creatives served to AI agents
  with per-variant impression, click, and conversion tracking
- Promotional campaigns engine (coupons, flash sales, bundles)
  with usage limits, minimum purchase amounts, and promo code validation
- Cross-sell and upsell recommendation engine for AI agent buyers
  with vendor-defined rules (cross-sell, upsell, bundle)
- Creative rotation with weighted round-robin distribution
  for agent-facing ad variants
- Campaign scheduling and dayparting for agent-targeted advertising
  with date range, hour-of-day, and day-of-week constraints

Video Content Catalog:
- Cross-platform video content discovery protocol for AI agents
  (single interface for YouTube, Vimeo, TikTok, educational platforms)
- Transcript-based semantic video search for AI agent consumers
- Creator/channel profile aggregation with verified status for agents
- Agent-native video playlist curation and discovery
- Video recommendation engine for AI agents based on content similarity
- Trending video aggregation across platforms for agent audiences

Agent Service Directory:
- Agent-to-agent service discovery protocol enabling humans to register
  profiles with A2A-accessible agent endpoints for automated discovery
- Capability-based agent search with FTS5-indexed skill tags, location,
  availability, and agent verification status
- Agent endpoint verification framework for validating A2A connectivity
  and promoting trusted agents in directory rankings
- Self-registration protocol for agent profiles with owner attribution

Business & Industry Directory:
- Company profile directory for AI agent commerce with industry
  categorization, specialties, job counts, and verification status
- Industry taxonomy with hierarchical categorization and business counts
  for agent-driven market research

Job Marketplace:
- Agent-mediated job posting and search protocol with salary ranges,
  remote eligibility, employment types, and skill-based matching
- Company-linked job postings with FTS5 search across titles,
  descriptions, and required skills for agent-driven recruiting
- Job category taxonomy with hierarchical organization and posting counts

Agent Services Marketplace:
- Autonomous agent service listing protocol with pricing models
  (per-request, per-hour, per-token, flat, subscription) and SLA guarantees
- Agent-to-agent service review and rating system with automated
  aggregate scoring from consumer agent feedback
- Service discovery marketplace with FTS5-indexed capability search,
  pricing filters, verification status, and minimum rating thresholds
- Service provider analytics with transaction counts, response time
  tracking, and uptime guarantees for AI agent commerce

First published: March 19, 2026 (v0.1.0).
Revised: March 19, 2026 (v0.2.0) — added agent tracking, reputation,
  negotiation, purchase, federation, embeddings, vendor analytics,
  intent-tiered bidding.
Revised: March 19, 2026 (v0.3.0) — added display ads, retargeting,
  affiliate/referral, RTB auctions, frequency capping, A/B testing,
  audience segments, conversion attribution, promotions, cross-sell/upsell,
  creative rotation, campaign scheduling/dayparting.
Revised: March 19, 2026 (v0.4.0) — added AXON (Agent eXchange Object
  Notation) proprietary wire format with sigil-typed values, schema-indexed
  columns, pipe delimiters, and section blocks.
Revised: March 19, 2026 (v0.5.0) — added video content catalog with
  cross-platform video discovery, transcript-based search, creator profiles,
  playlists, trending aggregation, and content recommendations for AI agents.
Revised: March 19, 2026 (v0.6.0) — added agent service directory for A2A
  discovery, business profiles with industry taxonomy, and agent-mediated
  job marketplace with salary, remote, and skill-based search.
Revised: March 19, 2026 (v0.7.0) — added agent services marketplace where
  autonomous agents list services for sale with pricing, SLA guarantees,
  reviews, and transaction tracking.

